Notes.Title: System Call Parameter Passing
Notes.Content: System call parameters can be passed through different methods: using registers, memory, and stack. When using registers, the parameters are directly placed into designated registers. In the memory method, a table is created to save data, which includes the addresses that are passed to the operating system (OS). With the stack method, parameters are pushed by the user process onto the stack, and then the OS pops these parameters off for processing.
